      "content": "# Analog sensor\n\nLetâ€™s introduce a new sensor to measure an ambient light level.  A photoresistor (aka light dependent resistor or LDR) would do a great job of measuring the parameter. However, there is a small problem: we do not have a photoresistor node in XOD.\n\nWe have primary nodes for working with the digital and analog ports of the Arduino. A photoresistor is a pretty primitive device, and all we need to do is read its value from the analog port on the Arduino. To do so, we use an `analog-sensor` node.\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. Assemble the [circuit with LDR and LED](https://xod.io/docs/tutorial/17-ldr/?utm_source=ide&utm_medium=ide_comment&utm_campaign=tutorial_17).\n\n2. Link the `VAL` output pin of the `analog-sensor` node to the `LUM` pin of the led node.\n\n3. Upload the patch to the Arduino.\n\nCover the photoresistor with your hand, and watch how the brightness of the LED changes.",
